    "causal_summary": "The upstream `dzianisv/opencode-plugins` repository ships an `auto-review` OpenCode plugin (branch `issue-136-package-auto-review`) that automatically dispatches a cross-model review session whenever an OpenCode session goes idle. The plugin demonstrates several design choices we have not adopted in our own ecosystem: event-driven activation via `session.idle` hooks, dynamic provider/model discovery via the OpenCode SDK, deterministic cross-AI family ranking, marker-based loop prevention, abort-race handling, and a structured PASS/FAIL/UNKNOWN checklist contract. We need to evaluate whether any of these patterns would improve our local skills (`sk-code-review`, `deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-agent-improvement`) and the OpenCode plugin ecosystem (`mk-skill-advisor`, `mk-code-graph`).",
